Define the sample in bcgsfhs_sample.sex.  Use read_bcgsfhs_sample() to
read it.

* Sky-subtract and pre-process the mosaics:
  bcgsfhs_skysubtract

* Cut out the BCG image and model:
  bcgsfhs_get_bcg, /debug
  
* Process Marc's BCG models and then do elliptical aperture photometry
  (see also BCGSFHS_BCG_MGE)
  
  

* Do a preliminary subtraction of the BCG (optional)
  bcgsfhs_bcg_mge

* Process everything through dimage
  * bcgsfhs_dimage, /parents, /stargal  